title: Jeannie (1941 - UK) delightful Scottish lass comedy
description:
Jeannie (1941 - UK)                                          aka Girl in Distress

Comedy / Drama / Romance

starring . . . . Barbara Mullen, Wilfrid Lawson, Gus McNaughton, Michael Redgrave
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0033769/


Every now and then, thank heaven, there comes a modest and unsung little film that arouses no anticipations at all and then quietly and firmly captivates you. Jeannie is just such a film, for Jeannie - and where has it been kept since it was made in 1941 - is as enchanting a bit of rue and nonsense as we've succumbed to in many a month. Based on Aimee Stuart's London stage play about a hardy little Scots girl, Jeannie is pure comedy of character. And what refreshing comedy it is! Actually, it is nothing more pretentious than an inverted Cinderella story about a plain-faced, plain-spoken little maid who inherits the sum of Â£297, spends it all in a few bewitching weeks in Vienna, and after a dispiriting adventure with a fortune-seeking count, discovers that the commonplace is more rewarding in the long run. With its plethora of good cheer, the film was able to garner good reviews on both sides of the Atlantic.
